# Mongoose Models Rules — apps/api/models/
# Applies to: all Mongoose schema/model files

## MODEL FILE TEMPLATE
```typescript
import { Schema, model, type Document, type Model } from 'mongoose';

// 1. Interface for document shape (typed fields)
export interface IMessage extends Document {
  channelId:   Schema.Types.ObjectId;
  senderId:    string;        // UUID from PostgreSQL employees table
  content:     string;
  contentType: 'text' | 'file' | 'system';
  parentId:    Schema.Types.ObjectId | null;
  attachments: Attachment[];
  reactions:   Reaction[];
  mentions:    string[];
  editedAt:    Date | null;
  deletedAt:   Date | null;
  createdAt:   Date;
}

// 2. Sub-document interfaces
interface Attachment { url: string; name: string; size: number; mimeType: string; }
interface Reaction   { emoji: string; userIds: string[]; }

// 3. Schema definition
const MessageSchema = new Schema<IMessage>(
  {
    channelId:   { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Channel', required: true },
    senderId:    { type: String, required: true },
    content:     { type: String, default: '' },
    contentType: { type: String, enum: ['text', 'file', 'system'], default: 'text' },
    parentId:    { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Message', default: null },
    attachments: [{ url: String, name: String, size: Number, mimeType: String }],
    reactions:   [{ emoji: String, userIds: [String] }],
    mentions:    [{ type: String }],
    editedAt:    { type: Date, default: null },
    deletedAt:   { type: Date, default: null },  // soft delete — never hard delete
  },
  {
    timestamps: true,          // adds createdAt + updatedAt automatically
    collection: 'messages',    // explicit collection name
  }
);

// 4. Indexes — define here, NOT in Atlas UI
MessageSchema.index({ channelId: 1, createdAt: -1 });   // primary query pattern
MessageSchema.index({ senderId: 1, createdAt: -1 });
MessageSchema.index({ mentions: 1 });
MessageSchema.index({ deletedAt: 1 });

// 5. Export model (check if already registered — important for hot reload)
export const Message: Model<IMessage> =
  (mongoose.models.Message as Model<IMessage>) ?? model<IMessage>('Message', MessageSchema);
```

## RULES FOR ALL MODELS

### Required fields on every schema
- `timestamps: true` in schema options (auto createdAt + updatedAt)
- `collection: 'name'` explicit — don't rely on Mongoose auto-pluralization
- Soft delete via `deletedAt: Date | null` — NEVER hard delete audit logs

### Query rules
- ALWAYS `.lean()` on read-only queries: `Model.find(...).lean()`
- ALWAYS `.select('field1 field2')` — never retrieve all fields unnecessarily
- ALWAYS validate ObjectId before querying: `isValidObjectId(id)`

### Indexes required by collection
```
notifications: { userId, isRead, createdAt }, { userId, createdAt }
audit_logs:    { actorId, createdAt }, { action, createdAt }, { targetId }
push_subs:     { userId }, { 'subscription.endpoint' } unique per user+device
```

### AuditLog is special — APPEND ONLY
```typescript
// NEVER add update methods to AuditLog model
// NEVER call AuditLog.findByIdAndUpdate() or AuditLog.updateOne()
// Only: new AuditLog({ ... }).save()  OR  AuditLog.create({ ... })
```
